commit.message: Allow validators to be set for create / update
Added TestHelper nuspec, and added missing FluentMongo DLLs
Added dependency on Ormongo from Ormongo.IdentityMap
More intelligent loading and saving of attachments
Allow inherited classes to execute their own type of observer
Renamed finder methods to be more consistent with Ormongo's ActiveRecord roots
Added AfterInitialize event, and made Before* events cancellable
BeforeX events can now be cancelled
Implemented lazy loading for references_one and references_many relations
Removed proxy objects, now require users to inherit from AncestryDocument and OrderedAncestryDocument. Hugely simplifies the code.
Added tests (and fixed implementation) for setting default position
Slightly better way of handling change tracking in DataDictionary
Assign default ordering position before save
Can now set DefaultScope on Document
Can now create new children through Children property
IHasAncestry no longer requires any implementation
Rename Assocation -> EmbeddedDocument in class and test names
Cleaner interface for ExtraData and TransientData
Added TransientData and ExtraData properties to Document
A number of refactorings, and moving a node within the tree now updates it descendants
Added initial Ancestry implementation. Updated Mongo and FluentMongo libs.
Add collection counts to database statistics
Changed DropDatabase to DropAllCollections, more useful in integration tests, because it doesn't drop indices
Added TestHelper project - useful for running integration tests in projects that use Ormongo
Upgraded to new versions of NUnit, Mongo driver, and FluentMongo
Added a way to explicitly close the connection to MongoDB

Now using NuGet versions of Mongo driver and FluentMongo
Added Attachment.Deleting event
Split EmbeddedDocument so it can be used with or without its own ID
Add back Document.Saving event - shouldn't have deleted it

Up to 92% test coverage, according to dotCover
Refactored attachments
Now using 32-bit mongodb binaries so tests work on both x86 and x64
Renamed mongo bin folder to binaries to get around .gitignore (yes, could also have made local .gitignore, but I'm lazy)
Added simple validation plugin - not everyone but will want this, so ideally I'll make a way to enable / disable plugins at will, but this library is not that advanced yet.

Added Attachment class for wrapping GridFS access
Added IPlugin concept to keep the main Document class clean
